2. In this Act-                                                    lnlerpre-
                                                                     tation.
    “Clerk” means the Clerk of a House;
    “costs” includes fees, charges and expenses;
    “Court” means the Supreme Court;
    “House” means the Senate or the House of Represen-
         tatives as the context may require;
    “member” means a member of a House;
    “member concerned” means the member in relation to
        whom a petition is presented,
    “petition” means a petition authorized by this Act;
    “prescribed” means prescribed by rules of court.
